+@node seq
+@chapter Sequences with Prefixes
+
+Workspace to provide the next entry in a sequence.  Each sequence is a
+prefix and a count.
+
+@deffn Ōłć item ŌåÉ seqŌłåpostingŌłåref key
+
+Function returns the next item in a sequence with prefix key,
+'Invoice0001, Invoice0002 ...  for example.
+
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn Ōłć key seqŌłåset value
+
+Function sets the value of a given sequence.  Some do not like to
+start at zero.  Use seqŌłåset.
+
+@example
+      'foo' seqŌłåset 10001
+      t1ŌåÉ(ŌŖéseqŌłånext 'foo'),ŌŖéseqŌłånext 'foo'
+      t1
+foo10001 f0010002
+@end example
+
+@end deffn
+
+@deffn Ōłć countŌåÉ seqŌłånext key
+
+Function returns the next integer in the sequence
+
